1
00:00:45,254 --> 00:00:48,966
PERFECT CROWN

2
00:00:59,851 --> 00:01:00,978
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

3
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:02,980
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

4
00:01:03,563 --> 00:01:05,357
-When did I ever ask--
-Stop that.

5
00:01:05,941 --> 00:01:08,610
You didn't see a doctor
after what happened, did you?

6
00:01:14,491 --> 00:01:17,202
Don't you think
I'd be quite the supportive wife?

7
00:01:32,384 --> 00:01:33,385
What are you doing?

8
00:01:36,597 --> 00:01:37,681
Stay still.

9
00:02:12,591 --> 00:02:13,759
I saw a camera.

10
00:02:15,927 --> 00:02:16,928
Oh.

11
00:02:21,308 --> 00:02:23,352
Is it still there?

12
00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:35,614
Should we try that again?

13
00:02:35,697 --> 00:02:37,824
I think we can give them a better angle.

14
00:02:40,243 --> 00:02:41,453
Maybe like…

15
00:02:42,621 --> 00:02:43,622
Mmm.

16
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:46,708
Mmm.

17
00:02:48,168 --> 00:02:49,461
Mmm.

18
00:02:49,544 --> 00:02:50,545
Now.

19
00:02:50,629 --> 00:02:52,381
Come on.

20
00:02:55,717 --> 00:02:58,970
PERFECT CROWN

21
00:02:59,554 --> 00:03:01,473
EPISODE 4

22
00:03:02,474 --> 00:03:04,226
Did you see their kiss last night?

23
00:03:04,309 --> 00:03:05,936
They're totally in love.

24
00:03:06,019 --> 00:03:08,355
-It kept me up all night.
-So romantic.

25
00:03:12,025 --> 00:03:13,068
Let's just go.

26
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:16,822
Announcing Grand Prince I-AN.

27
00:03:34,464 --> 00:03:36,174
LOVE ACROSS SOCIAL DIVIDES

28
00:03:36,258 --> 00:03:38,260
LOVE DEFYING SOCIAL CLASS…

29
00:03:38,343 --> 00:03:39,928
…I-AN AND SEONG'S MIDNIGHT TRYST

30
00:03:40,595 --> 00:03:42,848
We can no longer delay
an official statement.

31
00:03:43,598 --> 00:03:45,434
This matter will cause public unrest.

32
00:03:45,934 --> 00:03:47,018
We should be cautious--

33
00:03:47,102 --> 00:03:48,645
Staying silent now

34
00:03:49,229 --> 00:03:50,730
would only make things worse.

35
00:03:53,024 --> 00:03:54,568
Are you hoping I deny it?

36
00:03:54,651 --> 00:03:56,570
Your honor is at stake here.

37
00:03:56,653 --> 00:03:57,904
A grand prince…

38
00:03:59,781 --> 00:04:02,284
may kiss a woman and then
dismiss it as a mere dalliance?

39
00:04:02,784 --> 00:04:05,454
Is this the honor
you wish for me to uphold?

40
00:04:05,537 --> 00:04:06,538
That maiden

41
00:04:07,581 --> 00:04:10,041
is a mere commoner of illegitimate birth.

42
00:04:19,342 --> 00:04:20,635
Make it public.

43
00:04:28,059 --> 00:04:31,146
As His Royal Highness stated,
this is a scandal by a grand prince.

44
00:04:31,772 --> 00:04:33,356
We must do damage control.

45
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:34,816
"Damage control"?

46
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,735
With that in mind,

47
00:04:37,736 --> 00:04:38,862
you should confirm it.

48
00:04:41,323 --> 00:04:42,574
However,

49
00:04:42,657 --> 00:04:45,786
you must state firmly
that there is no prospect of marriage.

50
00:04:46,703 --> 00:04:48,914
Say that your acquaintance
has only just begun,

51
00:04:48,997 --> 00:04:50,457
with no talk of marriage.

52
00:04:51,875 --> 00:04:54,377
That should minimize any uncertainty.

53
00:04:54,461 --> 00:04:55,587
Prime Minister Min.

54
00:04:55,670 --> 00:04:58,632
There's nothing unusual about a young pair
falling in and out of love.

55
00:04:58,715 --> 00:05:00,091
If we treat it lightly,

56
00:05:00,926 --> 00:05:02,219
it will remain that way.

57
00:05:05,722 --> 00:05:06,723
Let it be so.

58
00:05:06,807 --> 00:05:07,808
However…

59
00:05:10,268 --> 00:05:12,687
that maiden should move out
of your private residence.

60
00:05:12,771 --> 00:05:14,523
-Why?
-Your Royal Highness!

61
00:05:14,606 --> 00:05:18,360
Not only was she pelted with eggs
at her own home with private security,

62
00:05:18,443 --> 00:05:21,112
but she is also bearing the brunt
of every insult online.

63
00:05:21,196 --> 00:05:22,489
As if that were not enough,

64
00:05:23,198 --> 00:05:26,034
she was photographed behind the palace,
under palace security.

65
00:05:26,535 --> 00:05:29,162
If anything happens to her
because she was left alone,

66
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:31,414
will you answer for it?

67
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:38,380
We may end up parting ways,

68
00:05:39,881 --> 00:05:41,758
or she may become my future wife.

69
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:45,303
Your Royal Highness, how could you…

70
00:05:45,387 --> 00:05:47,347
My residence is already home to many.

71
00:05:50,725 --> 00:05:52,644
Attendants who maintain the grounds.

72
00:05:54,104 --> 00:05:55,605
The Royal Guard for my safety.

73
00:05:56,773 --> 00:05:58,567
And there are even cats
that roam in my garden.

74
00:06:00,235 --> 00:06:02,195
The addition of my lady to that list…

75
00:06:04,823 --> 00:06:06,741
will have little effect.

76
00:06:10,871 --> 00:06:12,622
Where will Your Royal Highness reside?

77
00:06:14,207 --> 00:06:17,627
If Ms. Seong is permitted to stay
at your private residence for her safety,

78
00:06:18,128 --> 00:06:20,130
then you must stay at the palace.

79
00:06:20,755 --> 00:06:22,841
If rumors spread
that the palace is divided…

80
00:06:25,051 --> 00:06:26,428
over a single woman,

81
00:06:27,512 --> 00:06:28,763
it will be a grave matter.

82
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:39,941
OFFICIAL STATEMENT

83
00:06:40,025 --> 00:06:41,693
This was approved?

84
00:06:42,611 --> 00:06:44,779
Is this how you chose
to handle the matter?

85
00:06:45,488 --> 00:06:49,326
-You must compose yourself.
-How can I?

86
00:06:51,161 --> 00:06:54,039
Even if marriage is ruled out,

87
00:06:54,539 --> 00:06:57,584
once the palace acknowledges them,
that woman will gain status.

88
00:06:58,293 --> 00:07:00,462
Public interest is already at its peak.

89
00:07:00,545 --> 00:07:02,464
Should he dare to include her
in state matters--

90
00:07:02,547 --> 00:07:03,798
If you knew as much,

91
00:07:05,467 --> 00:07:07,093
you should have exercised restraint.

92
00:07:09,262 --> 00:07:12,057
Had you just left it alone,
the matter would've resolved itself.

93
00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:13,975
Criticism was already pouring in.

94
00:07:14,059 --> 00:07:17,103
"Failure to uphold the dignity
of his station and proper decorum."

95
00:07:17,187 --> 00:07:18,772
They had plenty of grounds.

96
00:07:18,855 --> 00:07:20,065
However,

97
00:07:21,066 --> 00:07:24,027
because Your Majesty has opposed
the Grand Prince,

98
00:07:24,778 --> 00:07:26,988
public opinion has shifted in his favor.

99
00:07:27,072 --> 00:07:30,992
In fact, criticism of Your Majesty
has already begun to surface.

100
00:07:34,829 --> 00:07:36,122
Just give your approval.

101
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:41,252
I will take care of the rest.

102
00:07:42,253 --> 00:07:44,547
Do you have a plan?

103
00:07:46,633 --> 00:07:50,261
There is no shortage of noblemen eager
to become the Prince's father-in-law,

104
00:07:50,345 --> 00:07:54,099
and plenty in the business world are eager
to keep that woman in check as well.

105
00:07:57,811 --> 00:07:59,729
That is to say,

106
00:08:00,605 --> 00:08:03,108
should something happen,
it would hardly be a surprise.

107
00:08:07,612 --> 00:08:10,657
The Royal Secretariat
has just released an official statement.

108
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:13,368
In a royal first, the palace
has acknowledged a courtship

109
00:08:13,451 --> 00:08:15,120
that isn't an engagement or marriage.

110
00:08:15,203 --> 00:08:19,040
We'll discuss this with formal royal
spokesman, Professor Hwang Wookyeong.

111
00:08:19,124 --> 00:08:21,835
-Welcome.
-Hello, it's nice to meet you.

112
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:24,838
You have always maintained the stance…

113
00:08:24,921 --> 00:08:25,922
Hwang Wookyeong?

114
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:27,632
Don't you know who that is?

115
00:08:27,716 --> 00:08:31,177
He used to be a royal spokesman
before he got blacklisted.

116
00:08:31,261 --> 00:08:34,013
Come on, you must know him. Last year,

117
00:08:35,390 --> 00:08:36,850
he was the one who claimed

118
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:39,853
the late king's death
wasn't an accident, but a murder.

119
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:41,730
A nut who jumps to conspiracy theories.

120
00:08:41,813 --> 00:08:42,897
Be quiet.

121
00:08:42,981 --> 00:08:47,068
Many have noted that
this official statement is unprecedented.

122
00:08:47,152 --> 00:08:48,153
What do you think?

123
00:08:48,236 --> 00:08:50,989
I consider it to be
very befitting of the royal family.

124
00:08:51,072 --> 00:08:54,743
Castle Group's Seong Huiju
is a commoner and businesswoman.

125
00:08:54,826 --> 00:08:57,704
She is far from a traditional royal bride
by palace standards.

126
00:08:57,787 --> 00:09:00,832
But it would've been difficult
for the palace to deny the relationship.

127
00:09:00,915 --> 00:09:04,919
After all, there were
several definitive eyewitness accounts.

128
00:09:05,628 --> 00:09:07,547
So are you suggesting that

129
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:09,674
they had no choice but to recognize it?

130
00:09:09,758 --> 00:09:11,885
-That's correct.
-Then Grand Prince I-AN…

131
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:12,969
Seong Huiju.

132
00:09:13,053 --> 00:09:16,014
…and what is the likelihood of marriage?

133
00:09:16,097 --> 00:09:17,932
Marriage would be highly unlikely.

134
00:09:18,016 --> 00:09:20,769
Uh, I doubt the royal family
would accept a commoner,

135
00:09:21,686 --> 00:09:24,147
given their sensitivity about lineage.

136
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:27,776
Then how do you think
the royal family will proceed?

137
00:09:28,318 --> 00:09:31,780
I don't expect them to provide
any further comments on the matter.

138
00:09:33,198 --> 00:09:34,783
THE GRAND PRINCE CLIMBED
OVER A WALL

139
00:09:34,866 --> 00:09:36,993
I knew this would happen.

140
00:09:37,744 --> 00:09:39,871
I told you we should've tried again.

141
00:09:41,039 --> 00:09:42,415
Well, I just…

142
00:09:42,499 --> 00:09:46,044
This angle is totally off. Darn it.

143
00:09:46,127 --> 00:09:47,754
What, are we in elementary school?

144
00:09:47,837 --> 00:09:50,173
We look like toddlers smooching.

145
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:52,133
That's what you care about right now?

146
00:09:52,217 --> 00:09:53,885
-We kissed and--
-Your Royal Highness.

147
00:09:54,385 --> 00:09:55,720
Marketing only works

148
00:09:55,804 --> 00:09:59,724
when it's unbelievably sexy or shameless.

149
00:09:59,808 --> 00:10:00,850
"Courtship"?

150
00:10:00,934 --> 00:10:03,853
Wishy-washy words like that
will get us nowhere.

151
00:10:03,937 --> 00:10:05,313
A tryst at a hotel!

152
00:10:05,814 --> 00:10:07,273
That's sexy.

153
00:10:07,357 --> 00:10:09,150
Prince I-AN's shotgun wedding!

154
00:10:10,360 --> 00:10:12,529
That's shameless, right?

155
00:10:12,612 --> 00:10:16,157
Doesn't it sound tempting, like junk food?

156
00:10:40,598 --> 00:10:43,726
The quicker we get married,
the quicker we get divorced.

157
00:10:43,810 --> 00:10:45,812
Okay?

158
00:10:52,819 --> 00:10:55,864
Royal weddings are meant
to be conducted step by step…

159
00:10:55,947 --> 00:10:57,782
Do you have that much time to waste?

160
00:10:57,866 --> 00:10:58,992
I don't.

161
00:10:59,075 --> 00:11:00,243
I mean…

162
00:11:00,326 --> 00:11:03,288
Then what? Should we really make it
a shotgun wedding?

163
00:11:03,371 --> 00:11:05,415
-So it's sexy and shameless?
-Yes.

164
00:11:05,498 --> 00:11:08,376
When you pursue
a venture everyone opposes,

165
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:12,338
you can't give them time to object.

166
00:11:12,922 --> 00:11:14,257
With that in mind…

167
00:11:16,634 --> 00:11:18,052
Are you free now?

168
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:24,309
All of a sudden? Why do you ask?

169
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:31,691
I have a little time.

170
00:11:34,277 --> 00:11:35,820
Can I take you somewhere?

171
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:38,740
Let's speed things up a bit.

172
00:11:42,327 --> 00:11:43,328
Speed things up?

173
00:11:46,956 --> 00:11:47,999
That's enough.

174
00:11:48,625 --> 00:11:51,294
Do I look like a kindergartner to you?

175
00:11:52,212 --> 00:11:54,505
Stay still.

176
00:11:54,589 --> 00:11:56,841
Let's show them
what we're made of this time.

177
00:11:56,925 --> 00:12:00,762
Since when do people
show others up with their hair?

178
00:12:02,180 --> 00:12:05,600
You were in sweats in those photos
where you were caught sucking face.

179
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:09,729
They must be roasting His
Royal Highness for having terrible taste.

180
00:12:09,812 --> 00:12:11,189
It makes me so upset.

181
00:12:11,272 --> 00:12:12,982
What's wrong with his taste?

182
00:12:13,066 --> 00:12:16,653
I mean, he chose me.
He clearly has exquisite taste.

183
00:12:16,736 --> 00:12:19,614
And those sweats are super expensive.

184
00:12:19,697 --> 00:12:23,201
Gosh. You must be a bird lover.

185
00:12:23,284 --> 00:12:25,828
Just look at that magnificent bird's nest
on your head.

186
00:12:28,498 --> 00:12:31,584
-You did that on purpose. You…
-Stay still.

187
00:12:35,129 --> 00:12:38,007
You really want me to clear your day?
All of it?

188
00:12:41,302 --> 00:12:44,764
I'm just worried for your sake.
It'll make tomorrow brutal for you.

189
00:12:45,348 --> 00:12:46,516
And for me too.

190
00:12:46,599 --> 00:12:48,643
She wants to be Princess Diana.
What can I do?

191
00:12:49,269 --> 00:12:50,353
Princess Diana?

192
00:12:50,436 --> 00:12:53,606
As in Princess Diana from the UK?

193
00:12:53,690 --> 00:12:54,691
Jeez.

194
00:12:55,191 --> 00:12:58,194
All this fuss will die down with time.

195
00:12:58,278 --> 00:13:01,281
That's what the Queen Mother
is waiting for.

196
00:13:02,949 --> 00:13:04,367
I won't let that happen.

197
00:13:06,953 --> 00:13:08,121
Your Royal Highness.

198
00:13:46,242 --> 00:13:47,285
Ta-da.

199
00:13:47,368 --> 00:13:49,829
Isn't she stunning?
Like an angel come to life.

200
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:55,501
Sure…

201
00:13:55,585 --> 00:13:57,045
…ly not.

202
00:13:57,670 --> 00:14:00,214
You went for "spoiled princess"
and not an actual princess?

203
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:07,805
Is he for real?

204
00:14:11,601 --> 00:14:13,686
I told you this wasn't my vibe!

205
00:14:23,029 --> 00:14:24,030
I mean,

206
00:14:24,822 --> 00:14:27,241
he's dressed in a princely suit.
What's his problem?

207
00:14:27,325 --> 00:14:29,285
That's what I'm saying, bro.

208
00:14:29,368 --> 00:14:30,495
He is beyond difficult.

209
00:14:36,501 --> 00:14:37,710
My goodness.

210
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:01,692
Please give us a moment.

211
00:15:01,776 --> 00:15:03,402
-I shall quickly fix this--
-No need.

212
00:15:29,554 --> 00:15:30,763
Sorry about that.

213
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:52,660
Thank you so much.

214
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:02,837
Perhaps a bit too plain?

215
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:04,172
Really?

216
00:16:05,047 --> 00:16:06,340
Hmm.

217
00:16:06,424 --> 00:16:08,092
I see what you mean.

218
00:16:08,718 --> 00:16:12,346
He does look a bit dull and old-fashioned.

219
00:16:15,558 --> 00:16:16,684
What the…

220
00:16:17,977 --> 00:16:19,353
-What are you doing?
-Seriously?

221
00:16:19,437 --> 00:16:20,897
Are you feeling shy or something?

222
00:16:22,190 --> 00:16:23,858
A royal never feels shy… Oh.

223
00:16:23,941 --> 00:16:25,276
Just lose this.

224
00:16:25,359 --> 00:16:28,321
Losing the pocket square
makes it a little bit less dull.

225
00:16:29,071 --> 00:16:30,114
Better, right?

226
00:16:30,198 --> 00:16:33,951
No, I was actually talking
about you, Ms. Seong.

227
00:16:34,452 --> 00:16:35,703
Oh.

228
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:36,871
Me?

229
00:16:37,455 --> 00:16:38,623
That's not possible.

230
00:16:38,706 --> 00:16:40,458
How could you ever call me plain?

231
00:16:46,297 --> 00:16:47,340
I'm dazzling.

232
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:53,596
So pretty.

233
00:17:14,742 --> 00:17:17,328
Go, Castle!

234
00:17:17,411 --> 00:17:21,749
-Let's go, Sharks!
-Let's go, Sharks!

235
00:17:21,832 --> 00:17:24,210
-Come on, Sharks!
-Let's go!

236
00:17:29,340 --> 00:17:31,425
It's not too late to call the Royal Guard.

237
00:17:32,468 --> 00:17:34,095
We'd be better without them here.

238
00:17:37,932 --> 00:17:38,933
Your Royal Highness!

239
00:17:39,684 --> 00:17:40,685
Ooh!

240
00:17:41,185 --> 00:17:42,186
Here we go.

241
00:17:43,271 --> 00:17:44,730
Let's see here.

242
00:17:44,814 --> 00:17:46,190
CASTLE SHARKS' LUCKY CHARM

243
00:17:46,774 --> 00:17:49,402
Ooh, I have such a keen eye for detail.

244
00:17:49,485 --> 00:17:50,820
You're 2XL, right?

245
00:17:51,362 --> 00:17:53,239
If we wear matching outfits…

246
00:17:53,322 --> 00:17:55,700
-He cannot.
-Why not?

247
00:17:55,783 --> 00:18:00,538
His Royal Highness can't wear uniforms.
No expression of political views.

248
00:18:00,621 --> 00:18:02,915
This isn't politics. It's just sports.

249
00:18:02,999 --> 00:18:05,543
"A royal's private life
is never truly private,"

250
00:18:05,626 --> 00:18:06,877
is the palace's position.

251
00:18:11,215 --> 00:18:13,384
Matching outfits would create some buzz.

252
00:18:15,011 --> 00:18:18,306
-Then you can just wear it, Aide Choi.
-Really?

253
00:18:18,389 --> 00:18:21,434
-It's so much more fun to cheer in this!
-So excited!

254
00:18:22,727 --> 00:18:25,521
Your Royal Highness,
remember I have warm undertones?

255
00:18:25,605 --> 00:18:26,647
This is perfect for me.

256
00:18:27,231 --> 00:18:28,858
-Huh?
-You're not wearing this.

257
00:18:28,941 --> 00:18:30,401
-Why not?
-Hmm?

258
00:18:42,788 --> 00:18:43,914
Hey, you!

259
00:18:44,665 --> 00:18:46,709
Why have you been ignoring my calls?

260
00:18:47,418 --> 00:18:48,419
Why you little…

261
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:50,546
Oh, His Royal Highness?

262
00:18:51,380 --> 00:18:52,840
Your Royal Highness.

263
00:18:52,923 --> 00:18:54,800
What brings you to such squalid grounds?

264
00:18:56,510 --> 00:18:58,095
Fried chicken?

265
00:18:58,179 --> 00:18:59,639
You're getting ahead of yourself.

266
00:18:59,722 --> 00:19:03,017
We don't speak until His Royal Highness
speaks to us first.

267
00:19:03,100 --> 00:19:04,226
Oh!

268
00:19:04,894 --> 00:19:06,687
Huiju has told me a lot about you.

269
00:19:07,271 --> 00:19:08,272
About me?

270
00:19:08,356 --> 00:19:09,357
What?

271
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:11,942
You better keep your trap shut.

272
00:19:12,652 --> 00:19:14,612
I wonder what she told you.

273
00:19:15,905 --> 00:19:17,073
Oh, right.

274
00:19:18,532 --> 00:19:19,659
Yes.

275
00:19:21,952 --> 00:19:25,122
It is an honor to make your acquaintance,
Your Royal Highness.

276
00:19:25,206 --> 00:19:26,916
I am Dayeong of the Han Family.

277
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:28,584
And your father's name?

278
00:19:28,668 --> 00:19:31,420
He is Jeongseok of the Han family.

279
00:19:32,129 --> 00:19:33,631
Former Minister of Justice.

280
00:19:34,799 --> 00:19:36,342
What a commendable father you have.

281
00:19:41,889 --> 00:19:42,890
Oh.

282
00:19:44,266 --> 00:19:45,976
Jeongwoo's throwing the first pitch?

283
00:19:46,060 --> 00:19:47,603
All right. Let's go!

284
00:19:50,773 --> 00:19:54,110
It appears we have Prime
Minister Min for the first pitch today.

285
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:55,194
That's right.

286
00:19:55,277 --> 00:19:57,321
He's famous for being
a hardcore fan of the Castle Sharks.

287
00:19:57,405 --> 00:20:01,951
I hear he even dreamed of being
a baseball player when he was young.

288
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:04,370
I'm excited to see
how his first pitch will turn out.

289
00:20:11,669 --> 00:20:14,588
That was
a beautiful pitch. Do you hear that crowd?

290
00:20:14,672 --> 00:20:16,757
The crowd is going wild for him.

291
00:20:16,841 --> 00:20:18,843
The crowd's love for Prime Minister Min is

292
00:20:18,926 --> 00:20:21,178
through the roof here
at Gocheok Sky Dome today.

293
00:20:21,262 --> 00:20:22,430
I couldn't agree more.

294
00:20:24,682 --> 00:20:26,058
Min Jeongwoo!

295
00:20:33,774 --> 00:20:35,151
Up to bat is Gang Suho.

296
00:20:36,610 --> 00:20:38,863
He pulled that one. It's high and deep.

297
00:20:38,946 --> 00:20:40,114
Is it going over?

298
00:20:40,197 --> 00:20:41,532
Over the wall and gone!

299
00:20:41,615 --> 00:20:43,993
Gang Suho pulls off a comeback win!

300
00:20:44,076 --> 00:20:45,786
Home run!

301
00:20:46,746 --> 00:20:47,830
Nanny Jung!

302
00:20:48,456 --> 00:20:49,498
You okay?

303
00:20:49,582 --> 00:20:52,001
The Castle Sharks
are sinking their teeth in…

304
00:20:52,084 --> 00:20:53,252
Are you all right?

305
00:20:55,045 --> 00:20:57,173
I am fine, Your Majesty.

306
00:20:58,299 --> 00:21:00,301
But the treat from Lord INPYEONG is…

307
00:21:01,093 --> 00:21:02,511
No need for concern.

308
00:21:06,307 --> 00:21:08,309
The corndog is safe.

309
00:21:09,518 --> 00:21:11,353
It certainly is not, Your Majesty!

310
00:21:11,854 --> 00:21:13,564
If we take a look, the stands are packed

311
00:21:13,647 --> 00:21:15,149
with fans in Castle Sharks jerseys…

312
00:21:17,443 --> 00:21:19,987
Your Royal Highness.

313
00:21:20,571 --> 00:21:22,072
-The Sharks…
-Stop it, babe.

314
00:21:22,156 --> 00:21:24,575
Get lost.

315
00:21:24,658 --> 00:21:26,702
Let's go, Gang Suho!

316
00:21:26,786 --> 00:21:28,829
You got this, Sharks!

317
00:21:30,623 --> 00:21:31,624
Your Royal Highness.

318
00:21:32,208 --> 00:21:33,209
Jeongwoo.

319
00:21:34,001 --> 00:21:36,962
You didn't leave after the first pitch?
I thought you'd already left.

320
00:21:37,546 --> 00:21:39,423
My secretary said
not to waste the photo op.

321
00:21:39,507 --> 00:21:41,091
Photo op?

322
00:21:49,141 --> 00:21:51,560
Scooch over, Your Royal Highness.
Jeongwoo needs a seat.

323
00:21:55,397 --> 00:21:56,398
Scooch over.

324
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:00,528
Come sit here, Jeongwoo.

325
00:22:05,991 --> 00:22:07,201
You should have some too.

326
00:22:08,035 --> 00:22:09,119
No, thank you.

327
00:22:09,203 --> 00:22:10,204
You're not hungry?

328
00:22:11,288 --> 00:22:12,873
-I am.
-Then eat.

329
00:22:14,041 --> 00:22:16,001
Are you a picky eater?

330
00:22:17,211 --> 00:22:19,839
-It's not that…
-He can only eat at restaurants.

331
00:22:20,422 --> 00:22:21,549
Why?

332
00:22:21,632 --> 00:22:24,093
Because quality and safety
can't be guaranteed elsewhere.

333
00:22:24,593 --> 00:22:25,678
And it's quite unseemly.

334
00:22:28,180 --> 00:22:29,515
Am I expected to do that too?

335
00:22:30,015 --> 00:22:33,310
-Kiss!
-Kiss!

336
00:22:33,394 --> 00:22:36,772
-Kiss!
-Kiss!

337
00:22:36,856 --> 00:22:40,276
On the Kiss Cam,
we have the hottest couple of the moment.

338
00:22:40,359 --> 00:22:41,652
-That's right.
-It's them.

339
00:22:41,735 --> 00:22:42,736
Oh, my gosh!

340
00:22:42,820 --> 00:22:44,572
They really look great together.

341
00:22:44,655 --> 00:22:47,283
But I'm sure it won't be easy
for His Royal Highness to kiss

342
00:22:47,366 --> 00:22:48,659
-on the Kiss Cam.
-Right.

343
00:22:48,742 --> 00:22:50,661
-Kiss!
-No! Stop!

344
00:22:50,744 --> 00:22:53,289
-Kiss!
-No! They can't kiss!

345
00:22:53,372 --> 00:22:57,418
-Kiss!
-No kiss! Where's the camera?

346
00:22:57,501 --> 00:23:00,379
-Kiss!
-Kiss!

347
00:23:00,462 --> 00:23:03,674
-Kiss!
-No! They can't kiss! No kiss!

348
00:23:03,757 --> 00:23:05,217
No kiss!

349
00:23:05,301 --> 00:23:09,555
-Kiss!
-Kiss!

350
00:23:09,638 --> 00:23:12,099
-Kiss!
-Kiss!

351
00:23:12,182 --> 00:23:17,479
-Kiss!
-Kiss!

352
00:23:17,563 --> 00:23:18,731
MUST UPHOLD HIS DECORUM

353
00:23:22,401 --> 00:23:23,402
Sorry, we can't.

354
00:23:23,903 --> 00:23:24,904
No, we can't!

355
00:23:25,446 --> 00:23:26,530
We can't kiss.

356
00:23:39,084 --> 00:23:40,085
Hold on.

357
00:23:40,669 --> 00:23:43,964
How are we supposed to be photographed
if they're covering us like this?

358
00:23:45,799 --> 00:23:47,843
-Huiju, let's go get dinner.
-Yeah?

359
00:23:47,927 --> 00:23:49,136
We had corndogs already.

360
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:51,180
That's not enough to fill you up.

361
00:23:51,722 --> 00:23:53,265
Remember what you wanted last time?

362
00:23:54,016 --> 00:23:55,601
-Last time?
-Yeah.

363
00:23:56,518 --> 00:23:59,063
Mmm. Oh, that!

364
00:24:00,230 --> 00:24:01,231
Your Royal Highness.

365
00:24:02,274 --> 00:24:03,275
Yes?

366
00:24:03,359 --> 00:24:04,360
Back to the palace?

367
00:24:05,319 --> 00:24:07,029
-What?
-Go on without me.

368
00:24:07,112 --> 00:24:08,614
I'll have dinner with Jeongwoo.

369
00:24:08,697 --> 00:24:09,990
I shall join you.

370
00:24:10,699 --> 00:24:11,700
Pardon?

371
00:24:11,784 --> 00:24:15,162
We came here together, so wouldn't it
be odd if we left separately?

372
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:17,122
Hmm.

373
00:24:26,006 --> 00:24:27,007
Mmm.

374
00:24:36,016 --> 00:24:37,726
Bye!

375
00:24:55,911 --> 00:24:56,996
Prime Minister Min.

376
00:24:57,663 --> 00:24:58,831
Yes, Your Royal Highness.

377
00:25:00,499 --> 00:25:01,792
Slow day at the office?

378
00:25:03,460 --> 00:25:04,545
Pardon?

379
00:25:16,015 --> 00:25:17,558
Mmm, it looks so good.

380
00:25:18,809 --> 00:25:19,893
Please eat up.

381
00:25:24,898 --> 00:25:27,276
We can't eat before you take a bite.
Please, go ahead.

382
00:25:28,485 --> 00:25:30,195
You should've gone back to the palace.

383
00:25:30,279 --> 00:25:33,115
Hmm? What now? Is there another issue?

384
00:25:33,615 --> 00:25:35,367
This is a restaurant, isn't it?

385
00:25:35,909 --> 00:25:36,994
I know.

386
00:25:37,077 --> 00:25:38,871
A royal shall never consume raw food.

387
00:25:38,954 --> 00:25:39,955
It's the law.

388
00:25:41,123 --> 00:25:43,917
Shall we order some gyeran-jjim
or doenjang soup for you?

389
00:25:44,501 --> 00:25:45,711
-No need.
-Wait, hold on.

390
00:25:45,794 --> 00:25:47,880
So, raw food? Nothing raw?

391
00:25:47,963 --> 00:25:50,716
Not even beef tartare?
You can't have anything like that?

392
00:25:50,799 --> 00:25:52,968
I cannot.
The risk of food poisoning is too high.

393
00:25:54,636 --> 00:25:55,763
What a load of crap.

394
00:25:56,555 --> 00:25:57,556
Load of…

395
00:25:59,767 --> 00:26:02,478
-A load of crap…
-You can't have street food.

396
00:26:02,561 --> 00:26:04,063
Nothing raw either.

397
00:26:04,146 --> 00:26:06,440
Where are you supposed
to find the joy in life?

398
00:26:07,232 --> 00:26:09,485
That's why you shouldn't marry
His Royal Highness.

399
00:26:09,568 --> 00:26:10,652
Too many restrictions.

400
00:26:11,945 --> 00:26:14,281
What else? What else can't you do?

401
00:26:25,834 --> 00:26:27,252
Here I am.

402
00:26:30,631 --> 00:26:31,840
Should we do this puzzle?

403
00:26:31,924 --> 00:26:35,135
Hwan, may I try on your Dragon Robe?

404
00:26:35,219 --> 00:26:36,220
Sure.

405
00:26:41,100 --> 00:26:42,101
Let's see here.

406
00:26:43,727 --> 00:26:45,938
Whoa, you look great in it.

407
00:26:46,021 --> 00:26:48,482
-It looks good on me, right?
-Yeah.

408
00:26:49,733 --> 00:26:52,653
Father, Hwan said I could…

409
00:26:56,406 --> 00:26:58,117
How dare you mock

410
00:26:58,700 --> 00:27:01,161
the Crown Prince's authority!

411
00:27:13,590 --> 00:27:15,843
Do not wear red.

412
00:27:15,926 --> 00:27:17,261
That is the king's color.

413
00:27:18,220 --> 00:27:19,555
Do not walk ahead.

414
00:27:21,223 --> 00:27:22,683
The king always leads.

415
00:27:25,561 --> 00:27:27,896
Do not question anything.

416
00:27:29,731 --> 00:27:31,316
It is the king's command.

417
00:27:58,427 --> 00:27:59,720
Eat up while you still can.

418
00:28:00,971 --> 00:28:04,141
You won't be able to
after the royal wedding.

419
00:28:08,937 --> 00:28:09,938
Mmm.

420
00:28:15,652 --> 00:28:18,447
Mmm, so good. It's delicious.

421
00:28:21,116 --> 00:28:22,326
Your Royal Highness.

422
00:28:22,409 --> 00:28:24,161
Were you at a raw fish restaurant?

423
00:28:24,661 --> 00:28:27,205
-Do not worry. I did not eat any.
-And a baseball stadium?

424
00:28:27,289 --> 00:28:28,790
Do not worry about that either.

425
00:28:28,874 --> 00:28:30,125
No personal show of support.

426
00:28:30,208 --> 00:28:31,460
No security issues.

427
00:28:31,543 --> 00:28:33,253
It was unannounced, so no reporters.

428
00:28:33,837 --> 00:28:35,756
You should have maintained decorum.

429
00:28:35,839 --> 00:28:37,174
I did.

430
00:28:37,257 --> 00:28:40,010
What is the use if you maintain it,
when she will not?

431
00:28:40,093 --> 00:28:41,803
Because she has no reason to.

432
00:28:42,679 --> 00:28:44,640
She is not a member
of the royal family yet.

433
00:28:45,807 --> 00:28:50,062
Do you truly not see that her faults
will soon become your own?

434
00:28:51,897 --> 00:28:54,358
What on earth were you doing
while this unfolded?

435
00:28:58,528 --> 00:28:59,821
We have no other choice.

436
00:29:00,322 --> 00:29:01,573
I shall step in.

437
00:29:02,491 --> 00:29:03,492
And do what?

438
00:29:03,575 --> 00:29:06,995
Your Royal Highness cannot be
expected to know a woman's proprieties,

439
00:29:07,079 --> 00:29:10,707
and it would be improper
for the Queen Mother to step forward.

440
00:29:11,375 --> 00:29:12,918
That leaves only me, does it not?

441
00:29:13,669 --> 00:29:17,297
I… am afraid I do not understand.

442
00:29:17,381 --> 00:29:18,382
Please allow me

443
00:29:19,508 --> 00:29:21,176
to discipline her.

444
00:29:27,557 --> 00:29:30,060
Even palace attendants
who run wild like colts

445
00:29:30,143 --> 00:29:31,478
become well-behaved

446
00:29:32,062 --> 00:29:33,730
after I am done with them.

447
00:29:34,439 --> 00:29:36,024
Rest assured, Your Royal Highness.

448
00:29:39,820 --> 00:29:40,821
Goodness me.

449
00:29:42,948 --> 00:29:45,117
Such excellent news. I am so relieved.

450
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:47,828
I have full faith in you.

451
00:29:47,911 --> 00:29:49,788
Such excellent news indeed.

452
00:29:56,628 --> 00:29:59,506
Gosh, are you leaving already?
You need to have breakfast.

453
00:29:59,589 --> 00:30:01,425
It's okay. I normally skip breakfast.

454
00:30:01,508 --> 00:30:03,093
That simply will not do. Eat up.

455
00:30:03,176 --> 00:30:05,595
Special apple bunnies for you. Open up.

456
00:30:06,346 --> 00:30:07,472
There's some fuzz here.

457
00:30:08,056 --> 00:30:09,307
-It's okay.
-Open up.

458
00:30:12,686 --> 00:30:14,521
We can skip all this next time--

459
00:30:14,604 --> 00:30:16,356
-Have a lovely day.
-Have a lovely day.

460
00:30:17,774 --> 00:30:18,775
Hmm.

461
00:30:20,110 --> 00:30:21,111
Mmm.

462
00:30:51,725 --> 00:30:53,643
Oh, right. We met at the palace last time.

463
00:30:53,727 --> 00:30:55,771
I am Jinsook of the Choi Family.

464
00:30:55,854 --> 00:30:58,106
Feel free to address me
as Court Lady Choi.

465
00:30:58,690 --> 00:30:59,816
Court Lady Choi.

466
00:31:00,525 --> 00:31:01,777
Where are my manners?

467
00:31:04,988 --> 00:31:05,989
I am Seong Huiju.

468
00:31:06,990 --> 00:31:08,950
I am the head court lady
of Anhwadang Hall,

469
00:31:09,034 --> 00:31:10,535
the residence of the Grand Prince…

470
00:31:17,125 --> 00:31:18,335
Hey, Ms. Do.

471
00:31:20,128 --> 00:31:22,964
Of course, I'm on my way.

472
00:31:24,883 --> 00:31:26,551
Yes, I swear I'm on my way.

473
00:31:27,052 --> 00:31:29,805
I can see Umyeonsan Tunnel up ahead.

474
00:31:32,265 --> 00:31:33,809
I'm almost there.

475
00:31:33,892 --> 00:31:35,644
I see you, Ms. Do.

476
00:31:36,144 --> 00:31:37,437
I'm not lying!

477
00:31:38,563 --> 00:31:39,606
So?

478
00:31:40,148 --> 00:31:41,858
You just got in the car and left?

479
00:31:41,942 --> 00:31:44,236
Yes. Was it something urgent?

480
00:31:45,862 --> 00:31:47,906
Court Lady Choi must be irritated.

481
00:31:49,449 --> 00:31:50,742
Why?

482
00:31:53,954 --> 00:31:56,623
She has been biding her time to teach you.

483
00:31:58,625 --> 00:32:00,252
What exactly would she teach me?

484
00:32:00,335 --> 00:32:04,172
The overall protocols, history,
and hierarchy of the royal family.

485
00:32:04,256 --> 00:32:05,465
Things like that.

486
00:32:13,932 --> 00:32:15,058
Good morning, Ms…

487
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:17,811
That sounds like a waste of time.

488
00:32:19,020 --> 00:32:20,981
Fine. I'll take the lessons.

489
00:32:21,523 --> 00:32:23,108
I need to go. Bye.

490
00:32:29,865 --> 00:32:30,866
Wow.

491
00:32:32,951 --> 00:32:35,704
Are you sure
you two weren't close in school?

492
00:32:38,206 --> 00:32:39,541
What? Why?

493
00:32:40,041 --> 00:32:41,209
It's just that

494
00:32:41,751 --> 00:32:43,587
you two make such a cute couple.

495
00:32:52,971 --> 00:32:53,972
Cute couple, my foot.

496
00:32:56,808 --> 00:32:59,227
What? There's a lot to do today.

497
00:32:59,853 --> 00:33:01,313
You have a lot of meetings too.

498
00:33:01,396 --> 00:33:02,939
You couldn't trim it down a bit?

499
00:33:03,023 --> 00:33:04,816
I did. I trimmed a lot.

500
00:33:05,984 --> 00:33:08,153
Fine, let's hear it. Keep it very brief.

501
00:33:08,236 --> 00:33:12,032
First off, you have a new product testing
with the R&D manager in one hour.

502
00:33:12,115 --> 00:33:13,575
You have one hour to do that.

503
00:33:13,658 --> 00:33:14,659
One hour?

504
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:16,786
-For a new product testing?
-Yes.

505
00:33:17,287 --> 00:33:20,332
You have lunch with Gang Taehyun
from Castle Pharma at 1:00.

506
00:33:22,042 --> 00:33:23,710
Why would he have lunch with me?

507
00:33:23,793 --> 00:33:25,003
Isn't he in Taeju's circle?

508
00:33:25,086 --> 00:33:26,713
He joined yours as of yesterday.

509
00:33:26,796 --> 00:33:29,049
All of a sudden?

510
00:33:29,132 --> 00:33:30,717
Didn't you also kiss the Grand Prince

511
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:32,552
all of a sudden?

512
00:33:40,101 --> 00:33:41,144
Was he good?

513
00:33:41,228 --> 00:33:42,229
What?

514
00:33:42,312 --> 00:33:45,273
I mean, the cheeks were flushed.
Totally blushing for real.

515
00:33:45,357 --> 00:33:46,358
Hey, come on.

516
00:33:47,150 --> 00:33:49,819
I was really hot that night.

517
00:33:49,903 --> 00:33:51,863
That outfit is surprisingly warm.

518
00:33:53,573 --> 00:33:54,950
Not you.

519
00:33:55,617 --> 00:33:56,785
His Royal Highness.

520
00:33:57,619 --> 00:33:58,703
What?

521
00:33:59,371 --> 00:34:01,039
Did you get all fluttery too?

522
00:34:03,708 --> 00:34:04,751
Listen, Ms. Do.

523
00:34:05,252 --> 00:34:06,753
Do I look like a teenager to you?

524
00:34:06,836 --> 00:34:10,924
Why would I blush and get all fluttery
over a measly kiss?

525
00:34:11,007 --> 00:34:12,050
Don't make me laugh.

526
00:34:12,133 --> 00:34:14,552
I see. Not so great, huh?

527
00:34:15,053 --> 00:34:17,055
Then again, he has no dating experience.

528
00:34:19,182 --> 00:34:21,893
He has no dating experience?

529
00:34:21,977 --> 00:34:22,978
Really?

530
00:34:23,561 --> 00:34:26,147
He's never publicly dated anyone.
No tabloid rumors either.

531
00:34:26,731 --> 00:34:28,817
That's what you meant?

532
00:34:29,734 --> 00:34:30,986
You may be wrong about that.

533
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:32,070
Hmm.

534
00:34:32,612 --> 00:34:34,197
I guess he was surprisingly good.

535
00:34:34,281 --> 00:34:35,907
Yeah, he clearly knew his way around…

536
00:34:36,616 --> 00:34:39,077
Hey. That's not what I meant!

537
00:34:41,204 --> 00:34:43,206
I'm not sure what you meant, but I got it.

538
00:34:43,290 --> 00:34:44,958
Shall we get going now?

539
00:34:45,041 --> 00:34:46,376
Why? What now?

540
00:34:46,459 --> 00:34:48,795
We'll barely have enough time
for the tailor as it is.

541
00:34:48,878 --> 00:34:50,255
New clothes?

542
00:34:50,338 --> 00:34:51,339
For what?

543
00:34:52,007 --> 00:34:53,008
Prime Minister Min did?

544
00:34:53,091 --> 00:34:54,342
That's what I'm telling you.

545
00:34:54,843 --> 00:34:55,885
It hasn't…

546
00:34:56,928 --> 00:34:58,763
Could we have some privacy?

547
00:34:58,847 --> 00:35:00,056
Yes, sir.

548
00:35:05,478 --> 00:35:07,480
It hasn't been made public yet,

549
00:35:07,564 --> 00:35:10,483
but the PR team said
he invited Huiju to the roundtable.

550
00:35:10,567 --> 00:35:12,611
But even Father was never invited to that.

551
00:35:12,694 --> 00:35:15,405
Exactly! He threw money
and sucked up to them for an invite,

552
00:35:15,488 --> 00:35:18,325
but they treated him like dirt
because he wasn't a noble.

553
00:35:19,534 --> 00:35:21,995
Why would they invite Seong Huiju?

554
00:35:22,078 --> 00:35:25,749
Babe, what would you hate more?
Huiju moving up in society

555
00:35:25,832 --> 00:35:27,667
or becoming the heir to Castle Group?

556
00:35:28,460 --> 00:35:29,544
I hate both equally.

557
00:35:29,628 --> 00:35:32,213
But still, out of the two,
wouldn't the former be better?

558
00:35:32,297 --> 00:35:36,384
Do you really want to see me bow down
and address her as Your Highness?

559
00:35:36,468 --> 00:35:39,137
Babe, you need to step back
and see the bigger picture.

560
00:35:39,220 --> 00:35:42,515
She doesn't become "Her Highness"
just because she marries him.

561
00:35:43,058 --> 00:35:45,268
We may have to bow down a bit…

562
00:35:46,436 --> 00:35:48,146
-Hey, Han Dayeong. I--
-But!

563
00:35:48,730 --> 00:35:50,023
She can't run a business.

564
00:35:50,106 --> 00:35:52,651
Royals aren't allowed
to engage in economic activities.

565
00:35:54,152 --> 00:35:55,445
No, I still don't like it.

566
00:35:55,528 --> 00:35:58,031
What if she divorces him
after she becomes "Her Highness"?

567
00:35:58,907 --> 00:36:00,158
Babe.

568
00:36:00,241 --> 00:36:01,993
Have you ever heard of a royal divorce?

569
00:36:04,162 --> 00:36:05,455
I thought they could.

570
00:36:05,538 --> 00:36:06,623
If that were true,

571
00:36:06,706 --> 00:36:09,459
Grand Prince I-AN
should've ascended the throne.

572
00:36:09,542 --> 00:36:11,586
Wouldn't that have made more sense?

573
00:36:13,004 --> 00:36:14,005
Maybe you're right.

574
00:36:14,714 --> 00:36:17,801
-Babe, we should get a gift for Huiju.
-What?

575
00:36:17,884 --> 00:36:20,553
We'll back her up
and get her married off to the Crown

576
00:36:20,637 --> 00:36:22,722
so you can claim
Castle Group all for yourself.

577
00:36:26,476 --> 00:36:28,520
I don't know.

578
00:36:31,147 --> 00:36:32,148
Come on now.

579
00:36:33,900 --> 00:36:35,151
Who does Taeju belong to?

580
00:36:35,819 --> 00:36:36,820
To Dayeong.

581
00:36:38,029 --> 00:36:39,948
Who does Castle Group belong to?

582
00:36:43,118 --> 00:36:44,119
To me.

583
00:37:04,013 --> 00:37:05,473
You stopped driving it around?

584
00:37:06,558 --> 00:37:08,768
-What?
-The red open-top car.

585
00:37:08,852 --> 00:37:10,019
Mmm.

586
00:37:10,562 --> 00:37:11,646
Huh?

587
00:37:12,188 --> 00:37:13,606
Did the Prince tell you to stop?

588
00:37:14,941 --> 00:37:16,901
As if I would ever listen.

589
00:37:18,153 --> 00:37:19,571
It's in the shop.

590
00:37:19,654 --> 00:37:21,489
They have a pick-up
and drop-off service now.

591
00:37:22,365 --> 00:37:23,491
It broke down?

592
00:37:24,033 --> 00:37:25,452
But you just got that car.

593
00:37:25,535 --> 00:37:28,455
Yeah. Someone hit the bumper and ran.

594
00:37:28,538 --> 00:37:29,539
Who?

595
00:37:29,622 --> 00:37:30,957
How would I know?

596
00:37:32,250 --> 00:37:33,251
But then again,

597
00:37:34,127 --> 00:37:36,629
there are a lot of people
who'd like to crash my car.

598
00:37:47,682 --> 00:37:49,392
I'm back.

599
00:37:51,352 --> 00:37:52,687
Her Ladyship is here.

600
00:37:52,771 --> 00:37:54,939
-Let me help you.
-Your Ladyship!

601
00:37:55,023 --> 00:37:56,816
-I'll take that.
-No, I can carry them.

602
00:37:56,900 --> 00:37:58,067
Just let me.

603
00:37:58,151 --> 00:38:00,528
-Did you go shopping?
-Yeah. I can put those away.

604
00:38:00,612 --> 00:38:01,780
Did you have dinner?

605
00:38:02,655 --> 00:38:04,032
I had a light salad.

606
00:38:04,115 --> 00:38:05,492
Get Her Ladyship dinner first.

607
00:38:05,575 --> 00:38:06,743
-No, it's okay.
-Sure.

608
00:38:06,826 --> 00:38:09,370
-We made sujeonggwa earlier--
-You are late.

609
00:38:25,470 --> 00:38:26,721
I know it is late,

610
00:38:27,347 --> 00:38:29,557
but your royal education
cannot be delayed.

611
00:38:30,642 --> 00:38:32,018
I ask for your understanding.

612
00:38:33,770 --> 00:38:35,563
Yes, of course.

613
00:38:35,647 --> 00:38:38,233
I understand.
I understand indeed.

614
00:38:40,026 --> 00:38:41,820
Do not repeat yourself.

615
00:38:41,903 --> 00:38:43,363
It makes you look frivolous.

616
00:38:44,322 --> 00:38:45,490
Okay.

617
00:38:46,658 --> 00:38:48,535
Dragging out the ends of your words

618
00:38:49,202 --> 00:38:50,286
is also forbidden.

619
00:38:51,830 --> 00:38:52,872
Yep.

620
00:38:53,748 --> 00:38:56,876
Your education will be comprehensive.

621
00:38:56,960 --> 00:39:01,422
For your public role, you will learn
royal protocol, royal history,

622
00:39:01,506 --> 00:39:04,342
proper conduct, and the court hierarchy.

623
00:39:04,843 --> 00:39:05,844
For your private role,

624
00:39:05,927 --> 00:39:08,763
you will learn who to meet
and whom to avoid.

625
00:39:08,847 --> 00:39:10,265
What to say…

626
00:39:11,975 --> 00:39:14,602
and what not to say.

627
00:39:14,686 --> 00:39:16,896
Let us start with your posture.

628
00:39:27,282 --> 00:39:29,075
Your standing posture

629
00:39:30,326 --> 00:39:31,452
is good.

630
00:39:32,745 --> 00:39:33,746
Please walk.

631
00:39:34,497 --> 00:39:35,498
Up to there.

632
00:39:36,374 --> 00:39:37,458
Mmm.

633
00:39:43,214 --> 00:39:44,424
More energy.

634
00:39:56,811 --> 00:39:57,854
Stand up straight.

635
00:40:01,983 --> 00:40:04,569
Can you not even stand still?

636
00:40:17,832 --> 00:40:19,417
Though you are small in stature,

637
00:40:19,918 --> 00:40:21,419
do not bow your head.

638
00:40:22,503 --> 00:40:24,422
Posture is dignity.

639
00:40:24,505 --> 00:40:26,090
Do you understand?

640
00:40:27,091 --> 00:40:29,552
Yes, Queen Mother.

641
00:40:33,181 --> 00:40:36,142
No, that is not right.

642
00:40:37,936 --> 00:40:39,646
Let me show you one last time.

643
00:40:39,729 --> 00:40:41,022
Watch carefully.

644
00:40:44,233 --> 00:40:46,402
Like this.

645
00:40:46,486 --> 00:40:49,197
Extend your leg.

646
00:40:49,280 --> 00:40:50,406
Extend…

647
00:40:50,990 --> 00:40:52,200
Oh, dear.

648
00:40:54,077 --> 00:40:55,370
Right here.

649
00:40:55,453 --> 00:40:57,914
-It hurts right here, doesn't it?
-Yes, it does.

650
00:40:57,997 --> 00:40:59,958
You have so many knots here.

651
00:41:00,541 --> 00:41:02,460
This must hurt a lot.

652
00:41:02,543 --> 00:41:04,003
-Yes, a bit.
-Here too.

653
00:41:04,087 --> 00:41:06,255
-Does this hurt even more?
-That is right.

654
00:41:06,339 --> 00:41:08,257
Oh, my goodness.

655
00:41:09,133 --> 00:41:12,136
I've been doing Pilates for ten years,

656
00:41:12,220 --> 00:41:14,722
so I can just tell from someone's posture.

657
00:41:15,598 --> 00:41:19,143
-Now is not the time for this…
-No, now is exactly the right time.

658
00:41:19,227 --> 00:41:20,853
Let's try that once more.

659
00:41:20,937 --> 00:41:22,522
-All right.
-I'll help you.

660
00:41:22,605 --> 00:41:25,692
-Like this?
-There you go. Lift your leg and…

661
00:41:25,775 --> 00:41:27,110
Good.

662
00:41:27,193 --> 00:41:28,528
You said to leave it to you.

663
00:41:29,278 --> 00:41:30,738
Is this how you discipline?

664
00:41:31,406 --> 00:41:32,615
Your Royal Highness!

665
00:41:57,432 --> 00:41:58,433
Hey.

666
00:41:59,308 --> 00:42:00,643
We have a lot of eyes on us.

667
00:42:01,728 --> 00:42:03,563
Please take her away.

668
00:42:04,772 --> 00:42:05,857
What?

669
00:42:06,774 --> 00:42:08,735
Do you know how much work I have to do?

670
00:42:08,818 --> 00:42:11,863
Must I devote my whole night
to posture correction?

671
00:42:14,574 --> 00:42:16,117
Your Royal Highness.

672
00:42:21,456 --> 00:42:23,750
What brings you to your private residence?

673
00:42:24,959 --> 00:42:26,878
I have been away from it for far too long.

674
00:42:27,545 --> 00:42:30,590
And I was curious to see
how your royal lessons were progressing.

675
00:42:30,673 --> 00:42:32,008
Please make your return.

676
00:42:32,091 --> 00:42:33,634
The palace gates will soon be shut.

677
00:42:41,225 --> 00:42:42,894
-You should come with me.
-Pardon?

678
00:42:42,977 --> 00:42:45,229
Your primary duty
is to protect Anhwadang Hall,

679
00:42:45,813 --> 00:42:47,356
not discipline her. Is that not so?

680
00:42:47,857 --> 00:42:49,942
-But Your Royal Highness--
-Do not argue.

681
00:42:50,026 --> 00:42:51,110
It is my command.

682
00:43:15,593 --> 00:43:17,220
With the Ancestral Rite concluded,

683
00:43:17,720 --> 00:43:19,680
we will begin planning the overseas tour.

684
00:43:26,145 --> 00:43:27,355
How many stops this year?

685
00:43:29,732 --> 00:43:31,359
It should be similar to last year.

686
00:43:36,072 --> 00:43:38,199
Why? Shall I reduce them?

687
00:43:38,783 --> 00:43:39,951
Won't you stop me?

688
00:43:42,078 --> 00:43:43,329
-What?
-My marriage.

689
00:43:44,539 --> 00:43:46,040
I thought you'd try at least once.

690
00:43:48,626 --> 00:43:49,669
I am not you.

691
00:44:02,473 --> 00:44:04,809
You may be able to decide something

692
00:44:04,892 --> 00:44:07,812
simply based on whether you find
something agreeable or not.

693
00:44:09,230 --> 00:44:10,565
But if I do that…

694
00:44:21,450 --> 00:44:22,910
the country would collapse.

695
00:44:23,494 --> 00:44:24,912
Checkmate.

696
00:44:28,457 --> 00:44:29,876
I'd rather you yelled at me.

697
00:44:36,257 --> 00:44:37,842
I handled the Junghwajeon incident.

698
00:44:40,344 --> 00:44:43,181
The Queen Mother should no longer
take issue with it either.

699
00:44:51,439 --> 00:44:53,191
In a royal funeral,

700
00:44:54,025 --> 00:44:57,987
the body is cleansed and an ablution
is performed at the Place of Passing,

701
00:44:58,696 --> 00:45:01,741
along with the ritual wailing,
the fencing, mouth-filling,

702
00:45:01,824 --> 00:45:03,826
and ice-bedding ceremonies.

703
00:45:03,910 --> 00:45:06,954
-The Royal Ancestral Altar--
-They really do all that?

704
00:45:08,164 --> 00:45:11,334
It is discourteous to interrupt.

705
00:45:11,918 --> 00:45:14,295
My apologies. I was just really curious.

706
00:45:14,921 --> 00:45:17,506
Did they do all that three years ago too?

707
00:45:18,174 --> 00:45:19,342
That is correct.

708
00:45:20,176 --> 00:45:21,594
Why don't I remember it at all?

709
00:45:23,095 --> 00:45:26,390
The last public funeral ceremony
held by the royal family

710
00:45:26,933 --> 00:45:28,726
was in 2005.

711
00:45:29,435 --> 00:45:30,436
Why?

712
00:45:32,688 --> 00:45:36,025
The mother of the Grand Prince,
Queen UIHYEON,

713
00:45:36,817 --> 00:45:38,903
passed away 20 years ago,

714
00:45:38,986 --> 00:45:41,572
in the fourth lunar month
of the Eulyu year.

715
00:45:48,037 --> 00:45:52,124
His father, King HUIJONG,
passed away seven years later,

716
00:45:52,208 --> 00:45:55,795
in the sixth month of the Imjin year.

717
00:46:06,722 --> 00:46:08,557
And just three years ago,

718
00:46:08,641 --> 00:46:10,559
His Majesty's father

719
00:46:11,143 --> 00:46:15,314
and Grand Prince I-AN's older brother,
King SEONJONG, passed away.

720
00:46:21,612 --> 00:46:23,364
With tragedies so frequent,

721
00:46:23,990 --> 00:46:26,534
the royal family decided
to keep the ceremony private.

722
00:46:30,246 --> 00:46:31,247
Your Ladyship?

723
00:46:31,330 --> 00:46:32,790
It's just all too much.

724
00:46:32,873 --> 00:46:34,959
-Pardon?
-It's no wonder

725
00:46:35,584 --> 00:46:38,087
His Royal Highness
has a chip on his shoulder.

726
00:46:38,587 --> 00:46:40,298
I mean, I knew all about it,

727
00:46:41,674 --> 00:46:43,592
but to hear about it one after the other…

728
00:46:48,222 --> 00:46:49,348
Don't mind me.

729
00:46:51,183 --> 00:46:52,977
I just want to be alone right now.

730
00:47:05,614 --> 00:47:06,949
QUEEN UIHYEON PASSED AWAY…

731
00:47:07,033 --> 00:47:08,326
"Queen UIHYEON

732
00:47:09,035 --> 00:47:11,245
passed away
in a vehicle rollover accident."

733
00:47:13,622 --> 00:47:14,665
KING HUIJONG PASSED…

734
00:47:14,749 --> 00:47:17,126
"King HUIJONG passed away
after a heart attack."

735
00:47:18,002 --> 00:47:19,879
"Could it have been prevented?"

736
00:47:23,966 --> 00:47:27,845
"King SEONJONG
tragically met his death in a fire."

737
00:47:38,105 --> 00:47:39,690
And if he suffers indigestion?

738
00:47:39,774 --> 00:47:41,067
You would be wholly to blame.

739
00:47:41,150 --> 00:47:42,777
And if Queen Mother is angered?

740
00:47:44,403 --> 00:47:46,530
Is that why he was so on edge back then?

741
00:47:55,373 --> 00:47:57,666
PRINCE

742
00:48:09,470 --> 00:48:10,513
Is he working?

743
00:48:19,605 --> 00:48:20,815
Please introduce yourself.

744
00:48:21,690 --> 00:48:24,360
She has been
my closest companion recently.

745
00:48:27,029 --> 00:48:29,031
I am Jaegyeong of the Kim Family,

746
00:48:29,532 --> 00:48:30,866
Your Royal Highness.

747
00:48:31,867 --> 00:48:35,538
There is a dinner
with the royal correspondents tomorrow.

748
00:48:36,705 --> 00:48:39,625
I cannot accompany you due to my illness.

749
00:48:39,708 --> 00:48:40,876
Take her in my stead.

750
00:48:42,002 --> 00:48:44,213
Her father is
the proprietor of Jeongui Daily.

751
00:48:44,797 --> 00:48:46,382
She will be able to aid you.

752
00:48:50,511 --> 00:48:53,764
You have been falling ill
quite frequently lately.

753
00:48:53,848 --> 00:48:56,434
Perhaps because I have had
a lot on my mind.

754
00:48:59,019 --> 00:49:00,187
Court Lady Im, approach.

755
00:49:02,773 --> 00:49:04,275
What is Her Majesty's ailment?

756
00:49:04,859 --> 00:49:05,860
Pardon?

757
00:49:06,819 --> 00:49:08,237
She has been ill for a few days.

758
00:49:08,863 --> 00:49:10,948
The royal physician must have visited.

759
00:49:11,031 --> 00:49:13,075
What is Her Majesty's ailment?

760
00:49:18,539 --> 00:49:20,166
You have failed in your duties.

761
00:49:20,708 --> 00:49:22,126
Not at all, Your Royal Highness.

762
00:49:24,420 --> 00:49:26,297
Instruct the royal physician

763
00:49:26,380 --> 00:49:29,383
to monitor Her Majesty's condition
three times a day.

764
00:49:29,967 --> 00:49:33,637
The illness may spread,
so private audiences must be forbidden.

765
00:49:34,305 --> 00:49:35,639
That includes Lord INPYEONG…

766
00:49:38,100 --> 00:49:39,727
and most certainly, His Majesty.

767
00:49:48,486 --> 00:49:50,362
You are unwell,
so you should get some rest.

768
00:49:50,946 --> 00:49:53,741
I shall attend the engagement alone.

769
00:49:59,788 --> 00:50:01,373
I feel terrible.

770
00:50:01,457 --> 00:50:04,043
It appears I have upset
His Royal Highness.

771
00:50:05,085 --> 00:50:06,212
Do not be troubled.

772
00:50:07,880 --> 00:50:09,840
Hunting inherently requires

773
00:50:11,008 --> 00:50:12,676
patience above all.

774
00:50:34,031 --> 00:50:35,783
That woman by the Queen Mother's side.

775
00:50:36,450 --> 00:50:38,702
Conduct a comprehensive
background check on her.

776
00:50:38,786 --> 00:50:39,787
Yes, sir.

777
00:50:40,579 --> 00:50:41,580
No.

778
00:50:43,123 --> 00:50:44,375
Start with Jeongui Daily.

779
00:50:44,458 --> 00:50:45,793
Look into them first.

780
00:50:45,876 --> 00:50:47,336
Understood, sir.

781
00:50:51,632 --> 00:50:52,633
Your Royal Highness.

782
00:50:53,175 --> 00:50:55,261
You have a missed call from Ms. Seong.

783
00:50:55,344 --> 00:50:56,345
Several, actually.

784
00:51:09,316 --> 00:51:11,485
THREE MISSED CALLS
JUNIOR ALUM

785
00:51:22,538 --> 00:51:23,539
Your Royal Highness.

786
00:51:23,622 --> 00:51:25,457
What do you need? I'm busy.

787
00:51:25,958 --> 00:51:27,876
Uh, I'm also really…

788
00:51:33,674 --> 00:51:34,967
Let's not get angry.

789
00:51:35,551 --> 00:51:37,845
You must take pity on this poor soul.

790
00:51:41,515 --> 00:51:42,516
Your Royal Highness.

791
00:51:43,100 --> 00:51:45,477
I'm only going to say this once,
so listen carefully.

792
00:51:46,854 --> 00:51:48,022
I'm on your side.

793
00:51:52,985 --> 00:51:57,323
What I mean is, I can only succeed
if you succeed as well.

794
00:51:57,990 --> 00:52:00,701
Husband and wife stand as one, right?

795
00:52:01,452 --> 00:52:04,997
I'm not saying this
because I adore you or anything,

796
00:52:05,080 --> 00:52:06,373
so don't get too excited.

797
00:52:09,918 --> 00:52:11,128
Are you still there?

798
00:52:12,046 --> 00:52:13,172
Hello?

799
00:52:14,840 --> 00:52:15,883
Your Royal Highness?

800
00:52:17,635 --> 00:52:18,636
Did he hang up?

801
00:52:19,178 --> 00:52:20,220
Oh, he did.

802
00:52:21,930 --> 00:52:22,931
Cool.

803
00:52:28,354 --> 00:52:30,356
JUNIOR ALUM

804
00:52:43,160 --> 00:52:44,912
-Choi Hyeon.
-Yes, Your Royal Highness?

805
00:52:48,499 --> 00:52:50,042
I made sure to run over.

806
00:52:50,125 --> 00:52:51,585
Did someone ask you to?

807
00:52:52,753 --> 00:52:53,879
Pardon?

808
00:52:53,962 --> 00:52:55,756
I will head to my private residence
in the evening.

809
00:52:56,590 --> 00:53:00,010
Uh, but Prime Minister Min
requested you stay in the palace…

810
00:53:00,803 --> 00:53:04,932
But where did he come up
with such nonsense?

811
00:53:05,683 --> 00:53:07,267
I shall prepare accordingly.

812
00:53:20,406 --> 00:53:22,574
-To the internet café!
-Remember last time…

813
00:53:26,078 --> 00:53:27,621
Your Majesty!

814
00:53:28,622 --> 00:53:30,791
-Are you all right, Your Majesty?
-Yeah.

815
00:53:31,291 --> 00:53:32,835
Behave yourself before His Majesty!

816
00:53:33,544 --> 00:53:35,003
My apologies, Your Majesty.

817
00:53:42,594 --> 00:53:43,846
You should be more careful.

818
00:53:43,929 --> 00:53:46,014
Yes, Your Majesty. Please get back safely.

819
00:53:47,266 --> 00:53:48,475
-Hey.
-Wait for me.

820
00:53:49,685 --> 00:53:50,728
This way, Your Majesty.

821
00:53:56,900 --> 00:53:59,403
What are you doing here,
Prime Minister Min?

822
00:53:59,486 --> 00:54:02,197
Today is not Sunday.

823
00:54:03,699 --> 00:54:04,950
I am aware, Your Majesty.

824
00:54:05,451 --> 00:54:08,328
Unfortunately, I must deal
with an urgent matter this weekend.

825
00:54:08,412 --> 00:54:11,790
I am afraid I must cancel
this Sunday's history lesson.

826
00:54:11,874 --> 00:54:13,834
Official duties must take priority.

827
00:54:13,917 --> 00:54:14,918
Instead,

828
00:54:15,586 --> 00:54:16,837
we will have a lesson today.

829
00:54:17,671 --> 00:54:20,674
Or we could just skip it.

830
00:54:26,472 --> 00:54:27,514
Come this way!

831
00:54:37,983 --> 00:54:39,485
I wish I could play.

832
00:54:49,620 --> 00:54:50,662
Prime Minister Min.

833
00:54:51,872 --> 00:54:52,873
Yes, Your Majesty?

834
00:54:53,457 --> 00:54:55,209
I would like to make a request.

835
00:54:59,671 --> 00:55:03,675
One, two, three, four.

836
00:55:03,759 --> 00:55:06,845
Five, six, seven.

837
00:55:06,929 --> 00:55:08,847
We keep a smile on our face.

838
00:55:08,931 --> 00:55:11,225
Smile. With elegance.

839
00:55:11,308 --> 00:55:12,351
There you go.

840
00:55:12,434 --> 00:55:15,103
One, two, three…
Straighten your back!

841
00:55:17,105 --> 00:55:19,024
-Again!
-Again. Go.

842
00:55:26,323 --> 00:55:30,827
We once again steady our breathing,
while maintaining a smile on our face.

843
00:55:31,328 --> 00:55:34,248
One, two, three, four.

844
00:55:34,331 --> 00:55:39,294
-Five, six, seven, eight.
-At this rate, she'll break all the china.

845
00:55:39,378 --> 00:55:41,838
I know, right? They're not cheap, either.

846
00:55:42,339 --> 00:55:44,508
But does that even help?

847
00:55:45,008 --> 00:55:46,760
I've seen it in period dramas before.

848
00:55:46,843 --> 00:55:48,971
-Put your arms down.
-I doubt it.

849
00:55:49,054 --> 00:55:50,389
Smile!

850
00:55:51,306 --> 00:55:52,432
Smile!

851
00:55:52,516 --> 00:55:54,226
There you go, with elegance.

852
00:55:55,018 --> 00:55:57,479
Six, seven, eight!

853
00:55:57,563 --> 00:56:00,691
One, two, three, four.

854
00:56:00,774 --> 00:56:03,735
Five, six, seven, eight.

855
00:56:03,819 --> 00:56:05,153
-Your Majesty!
-There--

856
00:56:06,113 --> 00:56:07,155
Hello, Your Maje…

857
00:56:16,331 --> 00:56:17,416
So you're saying

858
00:56:18,041 --> 00:56:19,543
you basically played hooky?

859
00:56:19,626 --> 00:56:20,794
How dare you!

860
00:56:20,877 --> 00:56:23,589
I am here to see Uncle.

861
00:56:24,089 --> 00:56:25,799
Did you make an appointment?

862
00:56:27,384 --> 00:56:30,846
Well… No, I did not.

863
00:56:30,929 --> 00:56:32,306
Exactly.

864
00:56:32,389 --> 00:56:35,017
You showed up
without even making an appointment.

865
00:56:35,100 --> 00:56:36,602
To play with your uncle.

866
00:56:37,227 --> 00:56:38,770
That's what playing hooky is.

867
00:56:42,941 --> 00:56:43,942
Well done.

868
00:56:45,027 --> 00:56:46,320
You only live once.

869
00:56:46,403 --> 00:56:48,113
You should play hooky at least once.

870
00:56:49,156 --> 00:56:50,324
Shall we?

871
00:56:57,956 --> 00:56:59,124
What do you want to do?

872
00:57:00,000 --> 00:57:03,170
He has been a bit overwhelmed recently.

873
00:57:04,212 --> 00:57:05,839
He's still young.

874
00:57:07,132 --> 00:57:09,426
If only there were
an age limit for being king.

875
00:57:10,385 --> 00:57:11,386
It's too bad.

876
00:57:13,847 --> 00:57:15,307
Yes…

877
00:57:18,727 --> 00:57:19,728
Sorry.

878
00:57:20,228 --> 00:57:22,731
My husband just wouldn't let me go.

879
00:57:22,814 --> 00:57:26,276
Hmm. You two dated for years,
and you still like each other?

880
00:57:26,360 --> 00:57:28,737
Of course. I like him more every day.

881
00:57:28,820 --> 00:57:30,489
He gets more handsome every day.

882
00:57:30,572 --> 00:57:32,491
And he treats me
better and better every day.

883
00:57:34,576 --> 00:57:37,788
As you should.
You abandoned your family to marry him.

884
00:57:38,580 --> 00:57:39,623
What?

885
00:57:40,666 --> 00:57:44,711
I mean, everyone knows you made
your father collapse when you got married.

886
00:57:44,795 --> 00:57:47,923
He threatened to disown you
and ban you from using the Han name.

887
00:57:48,423 --> 00:57:49,424
It caused quite a stir.

888
00:57:49,508 --> 00:57:50,759
Stop that.

889
00:57:50,842 --> 00:57:53,011
Nobody talks like that anymore.

890
00:57:53,095 --> 00:57:54,388
Oh, please.

891
00:57:54,471 --> 00:57:57,808
Everyone still judges people by status
and pedigree behind closed doors.

892
00:57:57,891 --> 00:57:59,226
We're just jealous.

893
00:57:59,726 --> 00:58:02,312
People like us would never dream of
marrying for love.

894
00:58:04,356 --> 00:58:06,733
I guess you have no idea
what's happening in the world

895
00:58:06,817 --> 00:58:09,069
because you're always cooped up
in your chambers.

896
00:58:09,152 --> 00:58:11,780
My sister-in-law, with her lowly pedigree,

897
00:58:11,863 --> 00:58:13,824
is dating the Grand Prince.

898
00:58:14,449 --> 00:58:15,701
Haven't you heard?

899
00:58:22,499 --> 00:58:23,709
What's wrong?

900
00:58:23,792 --> 00:58:24,918
That witch!

901
00:58:25,794 --> 00:58:28,046
Kim Jaegyeong was like that in school too.

902
00:58:28,130 --> 00:58:29,715
She's just so nasty.

903
00:58:29,798 --> 00:58:32,467
Maybe I should've just dragged her
out of there by her hair.

904
00:58:33,343 --> 00:58:34,928
You should have.

905
00:58:35,011 --> 00:58:36,638
What? Can I do that?

906
00:58:37,597 --> 00:58:38,932
Why not?

907
00:58:39,015 --> 00:58:41,977
Make sure you grab it next time.
I'll cover the settlement.

908
00:58:43,270 --> 00:58:45,021
My sweet husband.

909
00:58:45,564 --> 00:58:48,608
Of course. Money comes before dignity.

910
00:58:48,692 --> 00:58:50,110
This is why you make money.

911
00:58:54,489 --> 00:58:57,075
Here I go.

912
00:58:57,576 --> 00:58:58,618
Done.

913
00:58:59,661 --> 00:59:00,746
Good.

914
00:59:01,538 --> 00:59:02,539
All right.

915
00:59:05,959 --> 00:59:07,002
Now…

916
00:59:09,713 --> 00:59:12,174
you get three chances to hit this pebble.

917
00:59:12,257 --> 00:59:13,884
One, two, three.

918
00:59:13,967 --> 00:59:15,844
If it lands inside this circle,

919
00:59:15,927 --> 00:59:17,721
all this land becomes Your Majesty's.

920
00:59:17,804 --> 00:59:19,556
-Easy, right?
-It is.

921
00:59:22,601 --> 00:59:23,602
Jeongwoo!

922
00:59:28,190 --> 00:59:30,817
Min Jeongwoo!

923
00:59:35,697 --> 00:59:36,823
Yes? What do you need?

924
00:59:36,907 --> 00:59:38,158
Jeongwoo…

925
00:59:40,118 --> 00:59:42,996
Prime Minister Min,
you will be the referee.

926
00:59:43,622 --> 00:59:44,623
Me?

927
00:59:44,706 --> 00:59:46,708
The loser has to grant the winner's wish.

928
00:59:46,792 --> 00:59:49,127
Rock, paper, scissors.

929
00:59:49,211 --> 00:59:50,378
I won.

930
00:59:51,129 --> 00:59:52,130
Here we go.

931
00:59:52,214 --> 00:59:53,548
That's one.

932
01:00:09,439 --> 01:00:10,982
Got you!

933
01:00:11,066 --> 01:00:12,400
-I got someone!
-My goodness!

934
01:00:17,364 --> 01:00:21,493
Green light… Red light.

935
01:00:22,160 --> 01:00:23,578
Youngseon, you moved.

936
01:00:24,079 --> 01:00:26,706
Green light…

937
01:00:30,210 --> 01:00:32,879
One, two, three.

938
01:00:32,963 --> 01:00:35,799
-Four, five, six, seven.
-Five, six, seven.

939
01:00:35,882 --> 01:00:37,092
-One, two.
-One, two.

940
01:00:37,175 --> 01:00:40,345
-Four!
-Four, five!

941
01:00:40,887 --> 01:00:41,972
One, two!

942
01:00:44,558 --> 01:00:45,892
Well done, Your Majesty!

943
01:00:58,154 --> 01:00:59,322
Wow!

944
01:00:59,406 --> 01:01:00,866
I won!

945
01:01:02,951 --> 01:01:04,953
I said I won!

946
01:01:11,751 --> 01:01:13,003
You did not forget, right?

947
01:01:14,754 --> 01:01:15,755
What?

948
01:01:15,839 --> 01:01:18,300
You promised to grant me a wish.

949
01:01:19,301 --> 01:01:20,302
I said that?

950
01:01:22,012 --> 01:01:24,639
Are you a man of virtue or of profit?

951
01:01:30,145 --> 01:01:31,229
I remember.

952
01:01:37,694 --> 01:01:39,446
This is your wish?

953
01:01:40,030 --> 01:01:41,448
I saw it when I arrived.

954
01:01:42,157 --> 01:01:44,576
I have always wanted
to ride one with the wings.

955
01:01:45,368 --> 01:01:46,745
You cannot, Your Majesty.

956
01:01:46,828 --> 01:01:49,331
It is not an approved vehicle.

957
01:01:49,414 --> 01:01:53,293
But it is a car with wings!

958
01:01:53,376 --> 01:01:57,130
It's the only one in the country!

959
01:01:57,213 --> 01:01:59,049
Observing protocol is a matter of customs.

960
01:01:59,132 --> 01:02:02,260
It is the duty of a man of virtue
to uphold propriety and decorum.

961
01:02:02,344 --> 01:02:03,678
Have you forgotten?

962
01:02:16,274 --> 01:02:19,611
Why are you all saying
I cannot do anything? Why?

963
01:02:20,403 --> 01:02:22,822
I am the king!

964
01:02:22,906 --> 01:02:25,909
-I should be able to do what I want!
-My goodness, Your Majesty.

965
01:02:25,992 --> 01:02:26,993
What did you just say?

966
01:02:27,702 --> 01:02:30,956
His Majesty is at your private residence
with Prime Minister Min.

967
01:02:32,165 --> 01:02:33,291
What's he doing there?

968
01:02:33,375 --> 01:02:35,794
How would I know?

969
01:02:38,088 --> 01:02:41,299
You will be back
before the palace gates are shut, right?

970
01:02:42,634 --> 01:02:45,720
Be sure to keep your eyes on the road.
Don't forget your seat belt.

971
01:02:47,597 --> 01:02:49,057
Call me later, sir!

972
01:02:54,312 --> 01:02:55,563
Hmm.

973
01:03:01,569 --> 01:03:03,905
You must keep
the windows closed at all times.

974
01:03:03,989 --> 01:03:06,116
Yes, I'll be sure to keep them closed.

975
01:03:08,952 --> 01:03:10,120
Must you be the driver?

976
01:03:12,288 --> 01:03:14,791
It's the only one in the country.

977
01:03:14,874 --> 01:03:18,169
I don't want anyone else driving it.

978
01:03:20,672 --> 01:03:23,758
I will be in the escort vehicle
ahead of you and clear the road.

979
01:03:23,842 --> 01:03:25,760
You must not go above 60 km per hour.

980
01:03:25,844 --> 01:03:27,929
And you must stay on the phone with me.

981
01:03:28,471 --> 01:03:29,681
If, by any chance,

982
01:03:30,557 --> 01:03:32,726
an unexpected situation arises…

983
01:03:33,309 --> 01:03:34,644
Don't worry.

984
01:03:35,228 --> 01:03:38,356
I will put His Majesty's safety
above all else.

985
01:03:45,864 --> 01:03:48,324
-And the rear security detail?
-Have them follow me.

986
01:03:48,408 --> 01:03:50,744
I will follow behind Ms. Seong's car.

987
01:03:50,827 --> 01:03:52,412
You will?

988
01:03:52,996 --> 01:03:56,708
If security details surround her car,
people will assume it's a motorcade.

989
01:03:56,791 --> 01:03:58,376
It might attract spectators.

990
01:03:58,460 --> 01:04:00,170
If they discover His Majesty inside--

991
01:04:00,253 --> 01:04:01,588
No, that cannot happen!

992
01:04:03,798 --> 01:04:05,300
May I borrow a car?

993
01:04:05,383 --> 01:04:06,801
Something discreet.

994
01:04:31,409 --> 01:04:32,619
Are there any issues?

995
01:04:32,702 --> 01:04:34,704
No, we're fine.

996
01:04:34,788 --> 01:04:36,873
We're going too slow. That's the issue.

997
01:04:36,956 --> 01:04:38,958
Can we not go any faster?

998
01:04:50,553 --> 01:04:53,306
Let's go!

999
01:04:57,811 --> 01:04:59,187
What's wrong with this?

1000
01:05:07,028 --> 01:05:08,154
Your Majesty!

1001
01:05:09,197 --> 01:05:10,198
Damn it.

1002
01:05:16,913 --> 01:05:18,581
Your Majesty.

1003
01:05:18,665 --> 01:05:20,625
You have your seat belt on, right?

1004
01:05:35,056 --> 01:05:36,683
Seong Huiju, what's wrong?

1005
01:05:37,767 --> 01:05:38,893
Jeongwoo!

1006
01:05:39,477 --> 01:05:41,646
The brakes aren't working!

1007
01:05:49,237 --> 01:05:51,239
Your Majesty, close your window.

1008
01:06:43,499 --> 01:06:44,500
YANGSEO-GYO BRIDGE

1009
01:07:08,900 --> 01:07:10,693
Hang on tight, Your Majesty.

1010
01:09:03,765 --> 01:09:06,684
PERFECT CROWN

1011
01:09:43,304 --> 01:09:44,764
You even hurt your face?

1012
01:09:44,847 --> 01:09:46,641
When that's all you have going for you?

1013
01:09:46,724 --> 01:09:48,267
Someone messed with your car.

1014
01:09:48,935 --> 01:09:49,977
Let's reconsider this.

1015
01:09:50,061 --> 01:09:51,229
This marriage.

1016
01:09:51,312 --> 01:09:54,482
There has been nothing but trouble
since Prince I-AN entered your life.

1017
01:09:55,066 --> 01:09:56,359
Let's call off this marriage.

1018
01:09:59,362 --> 01:10:00,947
What the hell are you doing?

1019
01:10:01,531 --> 01:10:02,949
This is how you protect someone.

1020
01:10:04,158 --> 01:10:06,035
Just marry me instead.

1021
01:10:06,119 --> 01:10:08,037
Are you trying to protect that maiden?

1022
01:10:08,121 --> 01:10:09,122
SAY IT TO MY FACE

1023
01:10:09,205 --> 01:10:10,623
You never learned to bend.

1024
01:10:10,707 --> 01:10:12,166
Do not bend to their will.

1025
01:10:12,250 --> 01:10:15,086
Do not back away and do not compromise.

1026
01:10:16,671 --> 01:10:18,297
That's how you and I both

1027
01:10:18,381 --> 01:10:19,799
get what we want.

1028
01:10:25,972 --> 01:10:27,348
EPILOGUE

1029
01:10:27,432 --> 01:10:29,934
-Kiss!
-No! Stop!

1030
01:10:30,017 --> 01:10:32,478
-Kiss!
-No! They can't kiss!

1031
01:10:32,562 --> 01:10:35,064
-Kiss!
-No kiss! Where's the camera?

1032
01:10:35,148 --> 01:10:36,441
Should we speed things up?

1033
01:10:38,025 --> 01:10:39,068
Be sexy

1034
01:10:40,153 --> 01:10:41,237
and shameless?

1035
01:10:43,948 --> 01:10:49,370
-Kiss!
-Kiss!

1036
01:10:49,454 --> 01:10:55,918
-Kiss!
-Kiss!

1037
01:10:56,002 --> 01:11:02,216
MUST UPHOLD HIS DECORUM

1038
01:11:02,300 --> 01:11:03,342
Sorry, we can't.

1039
01:11:03,885 --> 01:11:05,094
We can't!

1040
01:11:05,178 --> 01:11:06,471
We can't kiss.

1041
01:11:44,425 --> 01:11:46,427
Translated by Justin S. Kim

1042
01:11:56,604 --> 01:12:01,442
PERFECT CROWN

